&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and maintain a comprehensive compliance program covering RIA, B/D, and 40 Act registered fund obligations, including all policies, procedures, testing, and supervisory controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor proposed SEC, FINRA, NFA, and CFTC rulemaking on an ongoing basis and translate regulatory developments into timely, actionable policy updates and business guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess compliance risk for all new products, funds, vehicles, and business lines prior to launch, delivering clear risk assessments and recommended controls to the CLO and relevant business leads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the marketing compliance and vendor due diligence programs, setting standards and maintaining accountability for outcomes while empowering team members to lead day-to-day execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as primary point of contact for the SEC, FINRA, and NFA, managing all examination logistics, document productions, and regulator communications from initial request through examination close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the regulatory relationships proactively, anticipating exam risk, ensuring audit-ready documentation at all times, and keeping the CLO apprised of open matters and remediation status.&lt;/li&gt;
